						<div class="postbody">He also says there's a &quot;strange&quot; 512-byte offset between sprite tile rows, and in another place that the interleaving of the sprite format depends on the sprite size.<br /><br />This stuff makes perfect sense if you think of sprite tables as 16x16-tile squares.  It's Famicom design heritage, presumably intended to make OBJ easy to mock up on a sheet of graph paper.</div>

